This patch is needed to prevent from NCL to be installed in an incorrect path, when the install
path contains a substring that is a literal arch definition. This is caused by the ymake macros
during configure, and in these cases the arch substring gets replaced by a "1", and the
destination paths end up deformed.

In my case I had:
My path   = /random/path/x86_64/software/NCL/6.6.2-foss-2023b

Which ended up being redefined as:
YMAKEROOT = /random/path/1/software/NCL/6.6.2-foss-2023b
etc.

As a solution, I store the arch value in a separate variable, while the paths are being defined,
and later I restore the original variable.

Author: Stamen Miroslavov <stamen.miroslavov@bsc.es>
Barcelona Supercomputing Center 2026

